0with%20a%20capacity%20to%20welcome%20400%2C000%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESramek%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20the%20city%20could%20have%20homes%20or%20apartments%20starting%20at%20%24400%2C000.%20The%20average%20home%20value%20in%20Solano%20County%20is%20about%20%24590%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjan-sramek-quits-goldman-2011-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eex-Goldman%20Sachs%20trader%3C%2Fa%3E-turned-City%20Founder%20said%20he%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20building%20a%20smart%20city%20or%20a%20libertarian%20utopia%2C%20but%20instead%20wants%20to%20address%20a%20persistent%20problem%20in%20the%20Golden%20State%20that%20is%20quality%2C%20affordable%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20800%2C00%20people%20left%20California%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20according%20to%20Census%20Bureau%20data.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-why-californians-are-leaving-the-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20cost%20of%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20one%20factor%20former%20California%20residents%20cited%20to%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year%20for%20their%20exodus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-affordable-housing-los-angeles-construction-regulations-lorena-plaza-delays-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E49-unit%20apartment%20complex%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20taking%2017%20years%20to%20build%20has%20become%20one%20recent%20example%20of%20the%20housing%20issue%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20walkable%20communities%20today%20%E2%80%94%20working%20families%20can't%20afford%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Sramek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20later%20added%20that%20the%20housing%20problem%20will%20only%20get%20worse%20with%20the%20advancement%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20arguing%20that%20this%20problem%20makes%20his%20project%20more%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20AI%20boom%20continues%20and%20the%20salaries%20continue%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20going%20to%20just%20increase%20the%20pressure%20on%20the%20housing%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20harder%20and%20harder%20and%20harder%20for%20working%20families%20to%20stay%20in%20San%20Francisco%20or%20in%20Palo%20Alto.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESramek%20didn't%20elaborate%20on%20what%20role%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20play%20in%20the%20housing%20crisis.%20A%20California%20Forever%20spokesperson%20didn't%20address%20the%20question%20in%20an%20emailed%20response%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20investigation%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.levernews.com%2Fartificial-intelligence-is-making-the-housing-crisis-worse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Lever%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20landlords%20could%20use%20AI%20to%20screen%20potential%20tenants%2C%20potentially%20opening%20the%20door%20for%20discrimination%20against%20people%20even%20with%20minor%20convictions%20such%20as%20littering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sramek%20appeared%20to%20be%20suggesting%20that%20AI%20will%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20wages%20%E2%80%94%20higher%20salaries%20to%20attract%20top%20talent%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20on%20people's%20ability%20to%20afford%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20blog%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FBlogs%2FArticles%2F2024%2F01%2F14%2Fai-will-transform-the-global-economy-lets-make-sure-it-benefits-humanity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Monetary%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated%20that%20AI%20could%20result%20create%20a%20split%20between%20workers%20who%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20AI%20and%20those%20who%20cannot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20may%20see%20polarization%20within%20income%20brackets%2C%20with%20workers%20who%20can%20