-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-1536x863.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-2048x1151.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-348177%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221156%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EGhongade%20overseeing%20the%20shrub%20removal%20work%20being%20done.%20Shrubs%20of%20morning%20glory%20had%20captured%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20banks%2C%20restricting%20water%20flow.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20always%20been%20fascinated%20by%20the%20river%20ever%20since%20my%20childhood.%20But%2C%20watching%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F321322%2Fstartup-duckweed-wastewater-treatment-river-rejuvenation-nature-based-solutions-lemnion-green-solutions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20mired%20in%20the%20silt%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20thickets%20with%20its%20banks%20being%20taken%20over%20by%20unwanted%20vegetation%2C%20disturbed%20me%20a%20lot%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20February%202011%2C%20Ghongade%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325386%2Fchangemakers-transform-polluted-water-bodies-idbi-bank-environment-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20group%20of%20eleven%20other%20likeminded%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20embarked%20on%20foot%20to%20study%20the%20165-km%20stretch%20of%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20ecosystem%20and%20understand%20what%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20with%20a%20river%20whose%20watershed%20area%20was%20around%204%2C763%20sq%20km.%20This%20group%20included%20a%20horticulturist%2C%20a%20botanist%2C%20an%20irrigation%20specialist%2C%20an%20educationist%2C%20a%20litterateur%2C%20an%20ex-serviceman%2C%20and%20a%20farmer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20undertook%20the%20trip%20to%20study%20the%20soil%2C%20water%20quality%2C%20its%20availability%20for%20irrigation%2C%20and%20the%20cropping%20patterns%20adopted%20by%20the%20farmers%20etc.%20While%20the%20days%20were%20spent%20around%20the%20river%2C%20we%20slept%20in%20panchayat%20offices%2C%20temple%20precincts%2C%20schools%2C%20community%20halls%20and%20even%20in%20farmers%E2%80%99%20homes%20at%20night%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Ashok%20Shinde%2C%20a%20horticulturist%20and%20member%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EChala%20Nadi%20La%20Zanuya%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(let%E2%80%99s%20get%20to%20know%20the%20river)%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20few%20kilometres%2C%20the%20team%20members%20took%20soil%20and%20water%20samples%20and%20planted%20indigenous%20varieties%20of%20trees.%20They%20also%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20villagers%20living%20around%20the%20river%20and%20educated%20them%20on%20its%20dismal%20state.%20They%20also%20explained%20their%20vision%20and%20the%20steps%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20restore%20Manganga.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20of%20the%2021-day%20trip%20was%20a%20slim%20book%20titled%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EParikrama%20Mangangechi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(Circumnavigating%20Manganga)%20which%20highlighted%20the%20status%20of%20the%20river%20and%20was%20sold%20to%20school%20and%20college%20libraries%2C%20students%2C%20professionals%20and%20farmers.%C2%A0%